DO  - 10.5465/amr.1984.4277404
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 684
EP  - 695
VL  - 9
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The properties of organized or team production affect three phenomena--free riding, shirking, and task visibility--that mediate the relationship between organizational structure and technology, on the one hand, and employee performance and satisfaction, on the other. Using transaction cost theory, a model of the expected effects of the mediating variables on organizational behavior is presented, and a set of derived hypotheses concerning the structure-technology-behavior relationship is developed.
AB  - The properties of organized or team production affect three phenomena--free riding, shirking, and task visibility--that mediate the relationship between organizational structure and technology, on the one hand, and employee performance and satisfaction, on the other. Using transaction cost theory, a model of the expected effects of the mediating variables on organizational behavior is presented, and a set of derived hypotheses concerning the structure-technology-behavior relationship is developed.
